    E_4/E_0 = 12 × C(n,4) × (n-4)² / (144 × C(n,4)²)
            = (n-4)² / (12 × C(n,4))
    n=5: (n-4)²/(12×C(n,4)) = 1/60 = 1/60 ✓
    n=6: (n-4)²/(12×C(n,4)) = 1/45 = 1/45 ✓
    n=7: (n-4)²/(12×C(n,4)) = 3/140 = 3/140 ✓

  *** THEOREM: E_4/E_0 = (n-4)² / (12 × C(n,4)) ***
  Equivalently: E_4/E_0 = (n-4)² × 4! / (12 × n(n-1)(n-2)(n-3))
